{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"30302","heading":"Purposes","label":"30302 Purposes","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/stIII/ch303","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was formerly classified to , The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.section 15602 of Title 42"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"establish a zero-tolerance standard for the incidence of prison rape in prisons in the United States;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"make the prevention of prison rape a top priority in each prison system;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"develop and implement national standards for the detection, prevention, reduction, and punishment of prison rape;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increase the available data and information on the incidence of prison rape, consequently improving the management and administration of correctional facilities;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"standardize the definitions used for collecting data on the incidence of prison rape;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increase the accountability of prison officials who fail to detect, prevent, reduce, and punish prison rape;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"protect the Eighth Amendment rights of Federal, State, and local prisoners;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increase the efficiency and effectiveness of Federal expenditures through grant programs such as those dealing with health care; mental health care; disease prevention; crime prevention, investigation, and prosecution; prison construction, maintenance, and operation; race relations; poverty; unemployment; and homelessness; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":null,"label":"9","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s30302","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs30302%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"reduce the costs that prison rape imposes on interstate commerce.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
